parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Alternator Failure Leading to Vehicle Fires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause a vehicle fire, which can lead to property damage, injury, or even death.
symptoms: Smoke coming from under the hood
burning smell
loss of power steering
stalling
and in some cases
a complete vehicle fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, posing a significant risk to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often without pressing the accelerator pedal
and may be accompanied by a jammed accelerator cable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Accelerator cable failure can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The accelerator cable becomes jammed
causing sudden acceleration
loss of control
and accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control system failure can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly while the cruise control is engaged
and may be accompanied by a malfunctioning accelerator cable.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Brake Line Failure due to Contact with Body Weld Seam
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The puncture of the rear brake line can cause a loss of brake fluid, leading to a failure of the braking system, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Sudden loss of braking power
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the braking system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerates despite applying the brakes
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
vehicle does not stop when brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of the airbag can cause injuries to the driver and occupants, and potentially lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The airbag deploys without any impact or collision
the airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle's crash sensors are faulty
the airbag module is malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power steering can cause the steering wheel to lock up, leading to a loss of vehicle control, which can result in accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the steering wheel locks up
the vehicle is hard to maneuver
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the occupant may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seat breaks or collapses
the seat does not remain in its fixed position
the seat does not provide adequate support.
